cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about object detection using deep learning techniques, specifically utilizing convolutional feature interrelationship. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new deep learning approach, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of high-level patterns in feature maps suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of region proposals and classification suggests the involvement of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible category as well.
